{(2)}(\\tau)$ obtains a minimal value for times $\\tau^* \\simeq\n\\omega_0^{-1}$. Close to this time, the second-order coherence remains below 1\nat temperatures where the Fano factor is already above 1. We identify realistic\nexperimental parameters that can be used to test the sub-Poissonian nature of\nthe radiation.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Sep 2015 20:14:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-11-18"}
